==English==

===Etymology===
Derived from the same stem as the foul-smelling carboxylic acid liberated in [[rancid]] [[butter]], ''[[butyric acid]]'' + ''[[-ane]]''.

===Noun===
'''butane'''

#An inflammable gaseous hydrocarbon, C<sub>4</sub>H<sub>10</sub>, of the marsh gas, or paraffin, or [[alkane]], series.

